Solr
It is a search engine platform from Apache.

Features:
- Full-Text Search
- Hit Highlighting
- Faceted Search
- Dynamic Clustering
- Database Integration
- Rich Document Handling
- Provide Distributed search
- Index Replication
- Highly Scalable
Solr 4 has NoSQL features too.

Solr is written in Java and runs in a servlet container like Tomcat or Jetty. It uses Java serach library 'Lucene' for full-text search and indexing. It has REST like  HTTP/XML and JSON APIs that make it usable from most programming languages.

You put documents into it over HTTP via JSON, XML, CSV or binary and you can query it using HTTP GET and receive JSON, XML, CSV or binary results
